text:
M-E, Forks remain ranked No. 1 in state rankings 
By wbng sports M-E, Forks remain ranked No. 1 in state rankings October 14, 2015 Updated Oct 14, 2015 at 6:30 PM EDT 
(WBNG Binghamton) After a blockbuster matchup in Class C in Section IV last weekend not much has changed in this weeks New York State Sportswriters Association football rankings. 
Top-ranked Chenango Forks remains ranked No. 1 in the state after the win over Newark Valley last Saturday. Despite the loss, the Cardinals only drop three spots this week. 
Meanwhile in Class A, Maine-Endwell remains the top-ranked team in the state after a big win over Section III's Corcoran last Friday.
